{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe introduction of clinical multi-agent systems into the healthcare sector marks a substantial advancement in improving care quality through sophisticated computational methods and in-depth data analysis.",
    "Modern medicine increasingly relies on advanced technologies to enhance patient outcomes, streamline clinical processes, and provide deeper insights into complex health conditions.",
    "These advancements are driven by the integration of Large Language Models [27] (LLMs) like ChatGPT [16], BioGPT [24], ChatDoctor [37], and Med-PaLM [28], which have shown considerable success in processing and understanding medical data, providing customized care, and offering insights into intricate health conditions.",
    "However, their use in clinical trials faces challenges, mainly due to their limited ability to access and integrate external knowledge sources, such as DrugBank [31].",
    "This research stems from the urgent need to fully utilize LLMs in clinical settings, going beyond the conversational skills of current models to include actionable and explanatory analysis leveraging extensive external data.Our study introduces ClinicalAgent, a new Clinical multi-agent system tailored for clinical trial tasks."
  ]
}